The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 September is 69,632 (8,025.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 September, there were 2,221 new confirmed cases (256.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 August, there were 2,492 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 11% (271 fewer cases).
